model_explanation: “only gave Bill bananas” means the only thing Sam gave Bill was bananas, so he could not also have given Bill grapes.
S1 restricts what Mary received (only apples), not who else received apples; giving Ellen apples is compatible.
S1 restricts what Sue received (only apples), not who else received apples; giving Tom apples is compatible.
if Bill got only grapes, then he didn’t get oranges.
if Bill got only apples, then he didn’t get bananas.
if Sue got only apples, then she didn’t get bananas.
S1 restricts what Ellen received, not whether Tom got oranges.
S1 restricts what Tom received, not whether Mary got apples.
S1 doesn’t restrict who else got apples; it only says Tom received only apples.
S1 restricts what Sue received, not whether Tom got bananas.
